instruction:
This code has an issue:
```
this.schedule(function() {
    if (gameOver) return;
    spawnEnemy();
}, 2.0);
```
Checking a flag every call instead of unscheduling. How should this be fixed?

output:
Instead of checking a `gameOver` flag every 2 seconds, unschedule the callback when the game ends. This saves the scheduler from calling a no-op function repeatedly and makes the code's intent clearer.

```js
this.schedule(this.spawnEnemy, 2.0);
// When game is over:
this.unschedule(this.spawnEnemy);
```

