instruction:
This code has a pattern that should be improved:
```
cc.spriteFrameCache.addSpriteFrames('res/a.plist', 'res/a.png');
cc.spriteFrameCache.addSpriteFrames('res/b.plist', 'res/b.png');
cc.spriteFrameCache.addSpriteFrames('res/c.plist', 'res/c.png');
cc.spriteFrameCache.addSpriteFrames('res/d.plist', 'res/d.png');
```
Repetitive resource loading calls. How can this be refactored?

output:
Use a data-driven approach with an array and loop. Adding a new atlas only requires adding one string to the array. This pattern is especially powerful when the atlas list is loaded from a config file.

```js
